The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), has said that Nigeria now has 51 confirmed cases of the Coronavirus (COVID-19 As at 11:25 pm on March 25, there are 51 confirmed cases of COVID19 in Nigeria-two discharged, one death. Of the 51 confirmed cases, are in seven states, 32 are in Lagos, ten in FCT, three in Ogun, one in Edo, one in Ekiti, one in Rivers, one in  Bauchi, one in Osun  and one in Oyo. Currently there are 471,821 confirmed cases in 198 countries and territories and 21,297 people have died so far from the coronavirus COVID-19 outbreak as of March 26,